  "russia1894-2025-2-0": { summary: "Q03 — Which interpretation gives the more convincing opinion about the significance of Stalin’s economic policies? [8m]", topic: "the significance of Stalin’s economic policies — which more convi", markScheme: "L4 (7-8m): Complex evaluation of BOTH interpretations with sustained contextual knowledge — evaluates relationship between them. L3 (5-6m): Developed evaluation of both. L2 (3-4m): Simple evaluation of one." },
  "russia1894-2025-3-0": { summary: "Describe two features of the Red Army’s role in the Russian Civil War (1918–21) [4m]", topic: "Describe two features of the Red Army’s role in the Russian Civil", markScheme: "4m AO1: 1m per feature + 1m per supporting detail. Two distinct features required." },
  "russia1894-2025-4-0": { summary: "In what ways did Stalin’s purges of the 1930s affect life in the Soviet Union? [8m]", topic: "In what ways did Stalin’s purges of the 1930s affect life in the ", markScheme: "L3 (7-8m): Developed explanation of multiple ways with causal links. L2 (5-6m): One well-developed way. L1 (1-4m): Simple statements." },
  "russia1894-2025-5-0": { summary: "Which was the more important reason for the Bolsheviks’ victory in the Civil War: Red Army strengths or White Army weaknesses? [12m]", topic: "Which was the more important reason for the Bolsheviks’ victory i", markScheme: "L4 (10-12m): Balanced argument with specific evidence for BOTH bullet points, clear overall judgement. L3 (7-9m): Addresses both but unbalanced. L2 (4-6m): One bullet only." },
  "conflicttension1939-2025-0-0": { summary: "Q01 — Describe two features of the Paris Peace Settlement / consequences of the Treaty of Versailles [4m]", topic: "Describe two: the Paris Peace Settlement / consequences of the Tr", markScheme: "4m AO1: 1m per feature + 1m per supporting detail. Two distinct features required." },
  "conflicttension1939-2025-1-0": { summary: "Q02 — How useful are Sources A and B to a historian studying the impact of the Treaty of Versailles on Germany and international relations [Source A = German cartoon; Source B = Lloyd George’s private letter expressing concern about harshness]? [12m]", topic: "Source utility: the impact of the Treaty of Versailles on Germany", markScheme: "L4 (10-12m): Developed evaluation of BOTH sources using content AND provenance (NOP: Nature, Origin, Purpose). Makes substantiated overall judgement. L3 (7-9m): One source developed with provenance + comment on second. L2 (4-6m): Partial. L1 (1-3m): Content only." },
  "conflicttension1939-2025-2-0": { summary: "Q03 — Write an account of how the League of Nations attempted to keep the peace in the 1930s [8m]", topic: "Account: the League of Nations attempted to keep the peace in th", markScheme: "L3 (7-8m): Narrative analysis linking causes and consequences across the period. L2 (5-6m): More than one development with some explanation. L1 (1-4m): Simple statements." },
  "conflicttension1939-2025-3-0": { summary: "Q04 — ‘The Nazi-Soviet Pact (August 1939) was the main cause of the Second World War.’ How far do you agree? [16m + 4 SPaG]", topic: "How far agree: The Nazi-Soviet Pact (August 1939) was the main ca", markScheme: "L4 (13-16m): Sustained, balanced argument; well-supported overall judgement. AO1 (knowledge) up to 4m — range, accuracy and relevance of factual detail. AO2 (analysis) up to 12m — sustained argument considering evidence both for and against the stated view. L3 (9-12m): Develops both sides; judgement attempted but may be asserted rather than substantiated. L2 (5-8m): Some analysis of one or more factors; limited balance. L1 (1-4m): Simple, generalised comments; mostly descriptive. | SPaG (up to 4m, separate from essay marks): 4m = consistent accuracy + specialist vocabulary; 3m = generally accurate; 2m = adequate, some errors; 1m = limited accuracy." },
  "elizabethanaq-2025-0-0": { summary: "Q01 — How convincing is Interpretation A about Elizabeth I’s management of the Catholic threat? [8m]", topic: "Interp A: Elizabeth I’s management of the Catholic threat", markScheme: "L4 (7-8m): Complex evaluation of interpretation using contextual knowledge to corroborate AND challenge. L3 (5-6m): Developed evaluation. L2 (3-4m): Some evaluation with knowledge. L1 (1-2m): Basic." },
  "elizabethanaq-2025-1-0": { summary: "Q02 — How convincing is Interpretation B about the impact of the Spanish Armada on Elizabeth I’s reign? [8m]", topic: "Interp B: the impact of the Spanish Armada on Elizabeth I’s reign", markScheme: "L4 (7-8m): Complex evaluation of interpretation using contextual knowledge to corroborate AND challenge. L3 (5-6m): Developed evaluation. L2 (3-4m): Some evaluation with knowledge. L1 (1-2m): Basic." },
  "elizabethanaq-2025-2-0": { summary: "Q03 — Explain why the threat to Elizabeth I from Catholic powers developed in the years 1568–1588 [8m]", topic: "Explain why: the threat to Elizabeth I from Catholic powers devel", markScheme: "L4 (7-8m): Complex explanation with two or more well-developed causal reasons linked analytically. L3 (5-6m): Developed explanation of two reasons. L2 (3-4m): One developed or two simple. L1 (1-2m): Simple statement." },
  "elizabethanaq-2025-3-0": { summary: "Q04 — ‘Elizabeth I managed her foreign policy more successfully than her domestic policy.’ How far do you agree? [16m + 4 SPaG]", topic: "How far agree: Elizabeth I managed her foreign policy more succes", markScheme: "L4 (13-16m): Sustained, balanced argument explaining the importance of at least TWO aspects; well-supported overall judgement. AO1 (knowledge) up to 4m. AO2 (analysis) up to 12m. L3 (9-12m): Explains at least two aspects; some analytical reasoning. L2 (5-8m): Some explanation of one or more aspects. L1 (1-4m): Simple, generalised comments." },
