  "ocrcrimepunishment-2018-0-0": { summary: "Q1(a) — Give one example of a crime that was punishable by death in medieval England (c.1250–1500) [1m]", topic: "Give one example of a crime that was punishable by death in medie", markScheme: "1m recall: give one specific, relevant example/reason/feature from the specified period." },
  "ocrcrimepunishment-2018-1-0": { summary: "Q1(b) — Give one reason why the number of crimes punishable by death increased in the early modern period (c.1500–1700) [1m]", topic: "Give one reason why the number of crimes punishable by death incr", markScheme: "1m recall: give one specific, relevant example/reason/feature from the specified period." },
  "ocrcrimepunishment-2018-2-0": { summary: "Q1(c) — Give one way that the prison system changed in Britain during the 20th century [1m]", topic: "Give one way that the prison system changed in Britain during the", markScheme: "1m recall: give one specific, relevant example/reason/feature from the specified period." },
  "ocrcrimepunishment-2018-3-0": { summary: "Q2 — Write a clear and organised summary that analyses how the purpose of punishment changed between 1500 and 1900. Support your summary with examples. [9m]", topic: "Write a clear and organised summary that analyses how the purpose", markScheme: "L4 (8-9m): Clear, organised analytical summary explaining how/why the development evolved, using well-chosen examples integrated into analysis. L3 (5-7m): Organised with examples but less analytical. L2 (3-4m): Partly organised. L1 (1-2m): Isolated points." },
  "ocrcrimepunishment-2018-4-0": { summary: "Q3 — Why did transportation to Australia become an important form of punishment in the 18th and 19th centuries? Explain your answer. [10m]", topic: "Why did transportation to Australia become an important form of p", markScheme: "L4 (8-10m): Developed causal explanation of why [change] happened, analysing two or more reasons with causal linkage. L3 (5-7m): Two reasons with some explanation. L2 (3-4m): One developed reason. L1 (1-2m): Simple statement." },
  "ocrcrimepunishment-2018-5-0": { summary: "Q4 — ‘Throughout the period c.1250 to the present, punishments have become less severe.’ How far do you agree? [18m]", topic: "‘Throughout the period c.1250 to the present, punishments have be", markScheme: "L4 (14-18m): Sustained analytical argument across the full thematic period, considers evidence both for and against the stated view, reaches a clear well-supported overall judgement. L3 (10-13m): Considers both sides. L2 (6-9m): Develops one or more factors. L1 (1-5m): Mostly descriptive." },
  "ocrcrimepunishment-2018-5-1": { summary: "Q5 — ‘The most important reason for the development of policing in Britain was the growth of towns and cities.’ How far do you agree? [18m]", topic: "‘The most important reason for the development of policing in Bri", markScheme: "L4 (14-18m): Sustained analytical argument across the full thematic period, considers evidence both for and against the stated view, reaches a clear well-supported overall judgement. L3 (10-13m): Considers both sides. L2 (6-9m): Develops one or more factors. L1 (1-5m): Mostly descriptive." },
