/* ---------- generic Edexcel GCSE levels-based mark scheme guidance ----------
   Applies to ANY 16-mark+SPaG or 12-mark extended-response question (the structure
   is the same regardless of topic/year): AO1 = knowledge, AO2 = analysis/judgement,
   split evenly across four levels. Paraphrased — describes the marking APPROACH,
   not topic-specific indicative content. */
const GENERIC_MS_16 = "Marked across four levels (1: 1–4, 2: 5–8, 3: 9–12, 4: 13–16), blending knowledge (AO1, up to 6) with analysis, evaluation and an overall judgement (AO2, up to 10) — the top levels need sustained, well-organised reasoning that builds to a justified conclusion, with the judgement's criteria explicitly applied, not just accurate detail. SPaG is graded separately out of 4 for accuracy and use of specialist terminology.";
const GENERIC_MS_12 = "Marked across four levels (1: 1–3, 2: 4–6, 3: 7–9, 4: 10–12), each blending knowledge (AO1, up to 6) with analysis and explanation (AO2, up to 6) — the top levels need a coherent line of reasoning that stays focused on the question throughout, supported by precisely-selected detail.";


